  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Chop your <strong>basa fillet[s]</strong> into large, bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped basa</strong> to a bowl, sprinkle over <strong>half</strong> your <strong>ground turmeric</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) and a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and<strong> pepper</strong>, then give everything a good mix up and set aside until later – this is your <strong>marinated basa</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1627025439990-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1627025439990-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1627025439990-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1627025439990-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1627025439990-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the basa is marinating, cut your <strong>cucumber[s]</strong> in half lengthways and then slice finely</p><p>Add the<strong> sliced cucumber</strong> to a bowl with your <strong>rice vinegar</strong>, 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and a generous pinch of<strong> salt</strong></p><p>Stir it all together and set aside until serving – this is your <strong>quick-pickled cucumber</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1627025008534-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1627025008534-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1627025008534-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1627025008534-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1627025008534-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>basmati rice</strong> and 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[390ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span><strong> cold water </strong>to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1627025029216-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1627025029216-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1627025029216-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1627025029216-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1627025029216-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the rice is cooking, bash your <strong>lemongrass stalk[s]</strong> with a <strong>rolling pin</strong>, remove the <strong>tough outer layers</strong> and chop the <strong>softer inner core[s]</strong> finely</p><p>Peel and roughly chop your<strong> shallot[s]</strong></p><p>Put everything into a <strong>food processor</strong></p><p>Chop<strong> half</strong> your <strong>red</strong> <strong>chilli[es] </strong>roughly and add to the <strong>food processor</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!), then finely slice the rest into rounds (save these for garnish!)</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1627025046214-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1627025046214-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1627025046214-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1627025046214-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1627025046214-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>flaked almonds </strong>and <strong>remaining ground turmeric </strong>to the<strong> food processor</strong> with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>soy sauce</strong>, <strong>ginger & garlic paste </strong>and a pinch of<strong> sugar</strong></p><p>Pulse until you're left with a slightly chunky paste – this is your<strong> Malaysian-style spice paste</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1627025063106-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1627025063106-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1627025063106-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1627025063106-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1627025063106-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Add the <strong>Malaysian-style spice paste</strong> to the<strong> </strong>pan and cook for 4-5 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add your<strong> tamarind paste</strong> with 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[130ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[170ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-copy-1627025581572-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-copy-1627025581572-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-copy-1627025581572-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-copy-1627025581572-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-copy-1627025581572-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>marinated basa</strong> and cook, covered, for 4-5 min or until the basa is cooked through</p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p><p>Meanwhile, chop your <strong>creamed coconut</strong> roughly (if required!)</p><p>Once the basa is cooked, add the <strong>chopped creamed coconut </strong>to the pan and cook for 1 min further – this is your <strong>Malaysian-style coconut basa</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-2-1627025606691-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-2-1627025606691-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-2-1627025606691-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-2-1627025606691-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-2-1627025606691-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> Malaysian-style coconut basa</strong> with the <strong>basmati rice</strong> and <strong>quick-pickled cucumber</strong> to the side</p><p>Garnish with the <strong>reserved chilli rounds </strong>(not a fan of spice? Just add a little!)</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
